  "texts": [
    "New classes of antibiotics inhibiting previously undrugged targets are needed to overcome pre-existing resistance mechanisms.",
    "The tethered tripeptide structure of MCPs is not expected to be susceptible to existing mechanisms of resistance.",
    "Indeed, these compounds are able to kill Acinetobacter clinical isolates displaying a wide range of resistance mechanisms.",
    "Moreover, MCPs inhibit the LPS-transport machinery LptB 2 FGC, which represents an antibiotic target in Acinetobacter.",
    "Antibiotics inhibiting a single target may have resistance liabilities 36 and, indeed, point mutations in LptF were identified at a frequency of ≤1 × 10 -8 at exposures ≤4× MIC, resulting in a high fold change in MIC."
